OL,5, Michael O'Reilly from Bexhill wants a  
OL,6, job, but says he can't find one because
OL,7, companies don't want people his age.   
OL,9,F"It's horrible," he says. "You feel    
OL,10,Fyour usefulness has passed."           
OL,12,FHis experience is not unusual. New     
OL,13,Fresearch from the Chartered Management 
OL,14,FInstitute (CMI) suggests firms are much
OL,15,Fless open to hiring older workers than 
OL,16,Fthey are to bringing in younger talent.
OL,18,FYet at the same time the chancellor is 
OL,19,Furging people who retired early to     
OL,20,Freturn to work.                        
